The paper deals with self-assembly systems, which are often studied in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. The use of geometric bumps and dents on the edges of tiles suggests a focus on Computational Geometry (cs.CG). The mention of algorithmic behavior and simulation of complex glue functions suggests a connection to the sub-categories of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
